'''''Temple Hill''''' by [[Drew Karpyshyn]] is the second novel in [[The Cities series]].

{{quote|''[[Elversult]], Site of [[Temple Hill]].'' 

''Among the dark streets of the city move thieves and cutthroats. And they don't like independent operators like [[Lhasha Moonsliver]]. But when she hires a former fighter, now the town drunk, as a bodyguard, she gets more than she bargained for. Together they'll have to battle the thieve's guild, the [[Cult of the Dragon]], and other, darker foes. And a fallen man will have to remember the proud warrior he once was.''|}}
